# --- Vercel: Preview + Production
# Every git push builds with env vars for that deployment type (Preview vs Production).
# Dashboard: Project → Settings → Environment Variables — set each key for Preview and/or Production
# (and Development if you use `vercel dev`). Vite bakes VITE_* in at build time.
# Typical split: same VITE_API_BASE_URL for both if one API; or staging URL for Preview, prod URL for Production.

# --- Browser (Vite) — prefix VITE_
# Base URL for reviewer API. Default in dev: same-origin /api (proxied to dev server).
# On Vercel static hosting, set full URL to your deployed **Reviewer** API (Express), ending in /api, e.g.
# https://your-reviewer-api.railway.app/api
# Omit for local dev (uses /api → Vite proxy to `VITE_DEV_API_PROXY_TARGET`, default http://127.0.0.1:8787).
# Do not point at the main DPAL filing API unless it also serves `/api/reviewer/v1/verifier/*`.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-reviewer-api.example.com/api

# Public DPAL web app URL — used to build “Open report” and “Open full chat in DPAL” links (?reportId=…&situationRoom=1).
# Example: https://your-dpal-front.vercel.app
# VITE_DPAL_PUBLIC_WEB_URL=

# Main DPAL API origin (same host as DPAL_UPSTREAM_URL, no path). Optional fallback so evidence <img> URLs that are still
# relative (/uploads/…) resolve to the filing server instead of the Vercel static origin.
# Example: https://web-production-xxxx.up.railway.app
# VITE_DPAL_MAIN_API_ORIGIN=

# Reviewer server proxies situation-room messages from the main API (GET /api/situation/:roomId/messages). Implement that route on the filing backend for chat in the Verifier “Situation chat” tab.

# Set to true to use bundled static mock data only (no network).
# VITE_USE_MOCK_DATA=false

# Optional Bearer token if your main DPAL / reviewer API requires auth.
# VITE_API_BEARER_TOKEN=

# Dev only: where Vite proxies /api (see vite.config.ts). Defaults to http://127.0.0.1:8787
# VITE_DEV_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8787

# Live dashboard: Server-Sent Events from the reviewer API (default on). Set to false to use polling only.
# VITE_REVIEWER_USE_SSE=true
# If SSE is off or fails, poll dashboard this often (ms):
# VITE_REVIEWER_POLL_MS=15000

# Server: how often to push dashboard over SSE (ms)
# REVIEWER_SSE_INTERVAL_MS=12000

# --- Validator AI (optional) — Reviewer API only
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Real outbound email (Reviewer API) — at least one provider:
# From address (required for Resend/SendGrid; for SMTP can use SMTP_FROM instead).
# You can use VERIFIER_FROM_EMAIL or RESEND_FROM (same effect for Resend).
# VERIFIER_FROM_EMAIL="DPAL Verifier <verifier@yourdomain.com>"
# RESEND_FROM=alerts@yourdomain.com
# Resend (recommended): verify your domain/sender to allow delivery to any recipient.
# onboarding@resend.dev is sandbox-only and can be restricted by Resend policy.
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_...
# SendGrid HTTP API (alternative)
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG....
# SMTP (alternative, e.g. Gmail app password, Mailgun, etc.)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=
# SMTP_PASS=
# SMTP_FROM=optional@override.com
# GET /api/reviewer/v1/health includes `email: { resend, sendgrid, smtp, fromSet }` (booleans, no secrets).

# --- Voice AI outbound calling (Twilio) — Reviewer API
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=+1xxxxxxxxxx
# Public base URL Twilio can reach for webhooks (required outside local tunneling):
# VOICE_WEBHOOK_BASE_URL=https://your-reviewer-api.railway.app
# Optional:
# TWILIO_MACHINE_DETECTION=Enable

# Fallback verifier label if the browser sends no X-Verifier-Identity header
# VERIFIER_DEFAULT_IDENTITY=ops@yourorg.org

# --- Reviewer API server (Node, server/index.mjs)
# Loads `.env` then `.env.local` (local overrides) from the project root when you run `npm run dev:api`.
# REVIEWER_API_PORT=8787

# --- Fix “Demo data (no upstream feed)” in the Validator UI ---
# Set the SAME API origin your main DPAL app uses (e.g. VITE_API_BASE). No trailing slash.
# Restart `npm run dev:api` locally, or set these on Railway/hosting and redeploy.
# For dpal-ai-server / Mongo anchors the feed is usually:
# DPAL_UPSTREAM_URL=https://web-production-xxxx.up.railway.app
# DPAL_UPSTREAM_REPORTS_PATH=/api/reports/feed
# Optional: DPAL_UPSTREAM_REPORTS_LIMIT=120
# Older generic JSON list: DPAL_UPSTREAM_REPORTS_PATH=/api/v1/reports
# DPAL_UPSTREAM_AUTH_HEADER=Bearer your-service-token

# Optional: base URL for public report links when upstream items do not include `url` / `publicUrl`.
# Same pattern as VITE_DPAL_PUBLIC_WEB_URL but on the API server (used when enriching queue rows).
# DPAL_PUBLIC_REPORT_BASE=https://your-dpal-front.vercel.app

# --- Verifier audit persistence (actions, timeline, notes, case state) — Reviewer API only
# Default (local dev): server/data/verifier-audit.json next to the server.
# On Railway: the filesystem is ephemeral — add a Volume, mount it (e.g. at /data), and set:
#   VERIFIER_AUDIT_PATH=/data/verifier-audit.json
# The Dockerfile sets this path; you must attach a Railway volume at mount path /data so survives redeploys.
# Alternative: VERIFIER_AUDIT_DIR=/data  (creates /data/verifier-audit.json)
